exportNdr(25.10)                                              exportNdr(25.10)

Name
       exportNdr  -  Exports/saves  the  new  rule  that  was created with the
       add_ndr command into a LEF/DEF file

Syntax
        exportNdr

       [-help]

       ndrRuleName

       {-def <defFileName> | -lef <lefFileName>}

       Exports/saves the new rule that was created with  the  add_ndr  command
       into a LEF/DEF file.  You can use this command after creating a non-de-
       fault rule.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each exportNdr parameter.  For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man exportNdr

       <ndrRuleName>
              Specifies the name of a non-default rule.

              Data_type: string, required

       -def <defFileName>
              Specifies the name of a DEF file, to which the non-default  rule
              is exported.

              Data_type: string, required

       -lef <lefFileName>
              Specifies  the name of a LEF file, to which the non-default rule
              is exported.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command exports the non-default rule, testndr to the  LEF
       file, all.lef.

       exportNdr testndr -lef all.lef

